text.text:
I don't even know how to start.... this is a total FRAUD for Mexican or Latin tourists, because the tours are especially focused on Italian tourists (like their owner, PIERO), we bought 2 tours, one in Manhattan, which was on the 20th. November, we arrived on time at the point where they appointed you to take us, the other tourists were arriving and we realized that they all spoke Italian... the guide called IDA arrived, she approached us and told us they speak Spanish, you know, and well, we did make a dissatisfied face. and he left with the Italian tourists, he came back and told us: they prefer that I speak only Italian or also Spanish, and well we said in Spanish (I mean we hired a tour in Spanish, not in Italian üòí) he made his uncomfortable and annoyed face again, She made us feel as if we had taken the wrong tour, we got on the bus and she told us to sit in the first places near her so she could "explain" us. She told us 2 or 3 things, like here is Central Park and yaaa, And the Italian tourists had a great explanation, great treatment, she made us feel like we were stinking, we got off the bus to the tour stops, and she didn't support us with photos, until I had to go ask her, she was the only one with the Italian tourists. , and we as if we did not exist, bad bad very bad! We told him that we had another tour, which was Contrasts, and he said well, it's not with me because that's a bigger tour and I almost think he told us, I'm not going to be speaking Spanish, you're going with another coach...

November 21, we arrived at the departure point the same way, and it was the same, although this time a larger group was divided into 2 buses and it was only Italian tourists... no other Latino or Mexican other than us, but on this occasion the guide named ANDREA, was much nicer, but in the same way the tour was always very focused on Italian tourists....
So if you are LATINO, and you want to know New York, I do not recommend this agency at all, do not waste your money here!
And to you Mi Viaje a Nueva York agency, stop falsely advertising that you run tours in Spanish, because it's just a LIE, and I demand a refund!

Ho partecipato al tour dei rooftop (terrazze panoramiche) sperando di poter vedere New York da posti insoliti.
Ho prenotato dall'Italia ed una volta arrivata a NY non ho fatto altro che presentarmi nel posto stabilito ed aspettare la partenza.
Il ragazzo che ci ha fatto da guida era molto preparato e simpatico, era giovane ed appassionato a quello che faceva.
Il tour prevedeva 3 rooftop diversi, il primo stupendo, con un'incantevole vista sull'Empire... gli altri due invece abbastanza scadenti, ma questi magari sono pareri soggettivi, quello che piace a me, non piace ad altri, e viceversa.
La nota negativa invece √® stata nel fatto che il pacchetto acquistato prevedeva sia uno spuntino di benvenuto appena giunti sul posto dell'incontro, sia degli stuzzichini in ogni terrazza, da accompagnamento ai drink... mentre a noi non √® stato offerto nulla a parte una bevuta quasi analcolica in ogni rooftop.
Il mio consiglio quindi √® di informarsi bene su internet su quali siano le terrazze migliori, organizzarsi da soli, e godersi insieme agli amici o alla persona amata, le spettacolari viste dall'alta di questa citt√† che tutti amano.
Nei rooftop una bevuta costa sui 10/15 dollari, quindi conviene!!

text.text:
I took the rooftop tour (panoramic terraces) hoping to see New York from unusual places.
I booked from Italy and once I arrived in NY all I did was show up at the designated place and wait for departure.
The boy who acted as our guide was very knowledgeable and nice, he was young and passionate about what he did.
The tour included 3 different rooftops, the first gorgeous, with an enchanting view of the Empire... the other two were quite poor, but these are perhaps subjective opinions, what I like, others don't like, and vice versa.
The negative note, however, was that the package purchased included both a welcome snack as soon as we arrived at the meeting place, and appetizers on each terrace, to accompany the drinks... while we were not offered anything apart from an almost non-alcoholic drink in every rooftop.
My advice is therefore to find out well on the internet about which are the best terraces, organize yourself, and enjoy the spectacular views from above of this city that everyone loves together with friends or a loved one.
In the rooftops a drink costs around 10/15 dollars, so it's worth it!!
